Gauteng brothers who consumed a drink laced with poison are being laid to rest. JOHANNESBURG -Â Three Gauteng brothers, who died after consuming a drink allegedly laced with rat poison, will be laid to rest. It's claimed the boys, aged 6, 13 and 16, were given the drink by their father. Two died at school after complaining about stomach pain. The third died en route to hospital. A fourth brother survived the alleged poisoning, as did the father, who has been charged with murder and attempted murder.